ProcedureHelp.#cdata:
Syntax: PROC PRTEXP<option(s)>;
      <SELECT printer_1 ...< printer_n>>;  
      <EXCLUDE printer_1 ... <printer_n>>; 

The PRTEXP procedure enables you to extract printer attributes from the SAS registry 
for replication and modification. PROC PRTEXP then writes these attributes to the SAS 
log or to a SAS data set. You can specify that PROC PRTEXP search for these attributes 
in the SASHELP portion of the registry or the entire SAS registry.

StatementHelp.#cdata:
Syntax: SELECT printer_1 ... <printer_n>;

The SELECT statement causes the output to contain information from only the printers 
that are listed.

Syntax: EXCLUDE printer_1 ... <printer_n>;

The EXCLUDE statement causes the output to contain information from all printers 
that are not listed.
